column5: Hey all.  My sister just messaged me asking if I know of any places in the Barrie area that sell's WWF/WWE T-shirts and stuff.  Her boys are into it now so she's looking for stuff for them.  Any help would be great.  For those of you that know her shop, go in and say hi to her (Laurie) and let her know where to look, thanks!  Geoff
Brian's got to know this for sure!

Now why would I know this stuff brudder?  Back when I was totlly into it. Iron Shiek,Boogie woogie man,Supa fly Snuka.My fav all time was Rowdy Rowdy Piper.He kicked butt.LOL  Best team dou was the BUSHWACKERS.      To answer your question Geoff,I havent seen anything but UFC stuff. Tell Laurie ,to check out the Koslov mall.There a sports/memorbila store there that has all types of shirts.  If I see anything,I,ll let you know.  BTW,After Bettys dentist appointment,were heading to her store.
Thanks Brian!  I just tried to get a hold of her to let her know, no answer...  I'll try again later and tomorrow.  Don't forget the coho. cake Brian...

I haven't seen any of those, but then I haven't been looking either.  I'll check the 400 Market this weekend as much as I can when I'm there, I know that there is a ton of licensed stuff (no further comment) in there.  I'll let you know Saturday evening if I find anything.  Michael
Walmart carries all kinds of licenced kids clothes. Go check it out, I would think they still carry WWF/WWE stuff.
Thanks guys.  I'll tell her to give those places a look, cheers.  Geoff
